title: Virgin Orbit to launch seven satellites for US Space Force and NASA
summary: Virgin Orbit is expected to launch the fifth flight of the LauncherOne rocket as early as 10:00 PM PDT on June 29 (05:00 UTC on June 30). The mission, named Straight Up, consists of seven satellites from the US Space Force and NASA that are destined for low Earth orbit.

title: SpaceX launches SES-22 C-band replacement satellite
summary: SpaceX launched the first television broadcast satellite under SES’s C-band clearing plan June 29 from Cape Canaveral in Florida.

title: NASA administrator tests positive for COVID
summary: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson has tested positive for COVID-19, he announced June 29, but is continuing to lead the agency as he isolates at home.

title: NASA to Industry: Let’s Develop Flight Tech to Reduce Carbon Emissions
summary: NASA announced Wednesday the agency is seeking partners to develop technologies needed to shape a new generation of lower-emission, single-aisle airliners that passengers could see in airports in the 2030s.
